│ I have reverted the previous patch. Now I will implement my new, more targeted heuristic. The idea is to make a `trunc` free only if it truncates a value from the  │
│ target's pointer-sized integer type and is part of an induction variable recurrence. This is a combination of my previous ideas but with a crucial constraint.      │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ The `DataLayout` can be obtained from `TheFunction->getParent()->getDataLayout()`. The pointer integer type can be obtained with                                    │
│ `DL.getIntPtrType(TheFunction->getContext())`.                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ The patch will look like this:                                                                                                                                      │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                              │
│   if (auto *TI = dyn_cast<TruncInst>(I)) {                                                                                                                          │
│     const DataLayout &DL = TheFunction->getParent()->getDataLayout();                                                                                               │
│     Type *SrcTy = TI->getOperand(0)->getType();                                                                                                                     │
│     if (SrcTy == DL.getIntPtrType(TheFunction->getContext())) {                                                                                                     │
│       auto *SE = PSE.getSE();                                                                                                                                       │
│       if (SE->isSCEVable(SrcTy)) {                                                                                                                                  │
│         const SCEV *S = SE->getSCEV(TI->getOperand(0));                                                                                                             │
│         if (const SCEVAddRecExpr *AR = dyn_cast<SCEVAddRecExpr>(S)) {                                                                                               │
│           if (AR->getLoop() == TheLoop)                                                                                                                             │
│             return 0;                                                                                                                                               │
│         }                                                                                                                                                           │
│       }                                                                                                                                                             │
│     }                                                                                                                                                               │
│   }                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ This seems like a reasonable heuristic that is specific enough to the pattern in the reproducer and less likely to break other tests.                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ I will now apply this patch.                                                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                             │
│ sed -i '6347a \                                                                                                                                                     │
│   if (auto *TI = dyn_cast<TruncInst>(I)) {\\\                                                                                                                       │
